Use tabindex of -1 to make an element focusable

If we add `tabindex="0"`, an element does become focusable, but it is also inserted in the tab order - even if there's no way to interact with it.

By setting the tabindex to -1, the element becomes focusable, but it does not receive focus when tabbing through the page.

See https://stackoverflow.com/questions/44909339/why-does-foundation-recommend-adding-a-tabindex-0-to-main-content

commit_list.message:
Don't store ratings in the database

Previously, we used to dynamically calculate the rating of a
service when fetching that service's data, and then insert that
rating into the database. This resulted in an insert query being
ran for every service listed on the homepage (i.e. every service)
when visiting the homepage.

A potential solution could be to recalculate the rating for the
appropriate service whenever a point is changed. This would mean
the service ratings would not have to be recalculated as often,
and you could theoretically fetch a service and its rating without
having to fetch all related points. However, since I'm not
well-versed enough in Ruby/Ruby on Rails yet, I don't quite know
how to do this by updating the Points model. Furthermore, I'm not
sure what repercussions it would have elsewhere in the codebase.

Since we were _already_ recalculating the grades whenever they
were needed, I've simply removed the `grade` column from the
database, and removed the logic that re-inserted it into the
database after every recalculation. This should solve at least
our most egregious performance issues on the homepage.

commit_list.message:
Remove ratings from points

Ratings are now deduced from the case linked to a point. I'm
hoping that this does not introduce too many performance issues due
to JOINing cases everywhere we need a point's rating (which I think
is pretty much everywhere), and that I managed to fix all the
places where a point's rating was referred to.
This also means that points without a case will no longer have a
rating. Be sure to backup the database before applying this, since
it will remove the rating column from the points table, including
all its contents.

Fixes #503, #504.

commit_list.message:
Only link to the annotation view with documents

In the service list, only show a link to the annotation view when
documents have already been defined for that service.
This has two advantages:

- Since adding documents currently requires knowledge of XPaths,
  this makes it easy for contributors to see which services they
   can immediately start annotating.
- For people who do understand XPath, it's easier to see which
  services should still have XPaths added to them.

Longer-term, when annotation is the default mode, we can probably
show them all the time again. In fact, it'd probably be the
default target when you click the service name.

Fixes #623.
